Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, ALT, and significant proteinuria with glucosuria and ketonuria, suggesting impaired renal function and possible liver involvement. Urine is brown, cloudy, with low specific gravity, but no evidence of infection. Findings are consistent with acute or chronic kidney disease, possibly with diabetic or metabolic involvement. Further clinical correlation and nephrology/hepatology evaluation are recommended.
